UseCase.dc:title: Auf ebenen und nicht geneigten Untergrund fahren

Requirement.dc:title: Head
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a head

Requirement.dc:title: Head Position
Requirement.dc:description: The Head of the Mars Rover shall be higher mounted than body, suspension and traction unit.

Requirement.dc:title: Head Function
Requirement.dc:description: The Head of the Mars Rover shall carry sensors and a LED Display.

Requirement.dc:title: Body
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a body

Requirement.dc:title: Suspension
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a suspension suspending the traction unit

Requirement.dc:title: Traction Unit
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a traction unit providing traction to the ground

Requirement.dc:title: Power Supply
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a power supply.

Requirement.dc:title: External Power Supply
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be operable with internal power supply only.

Requirement.dc:title: Internal Power Supply
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a power supply fulfilling all of the following conditions:* it contains an energy storage system* it contains an energy management system* it contains a power distribution system

Requirement.dc:title: Energy Storage
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have means to re-charde its energy storage system.

Requirement.dc:title: Available Power
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be operable for 4h under all of the following conditions:* The energy storage is fully loaded at the beginning* The operation requires less than or equal to 60% of the max energy in peak load* the environmental conditions are mission normal

Requirement.dc:title: Energy Re-Charging
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall re-charge the energy storage from 10% to 80% in 4h under the following conditions:* re-charging at mission normal conditions* no energy consumption of the Mars Rover since the re-charging period

Requirement.dc:title: Electrical Values
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall use 12 V DC voltage

Requirement.dc:title: Motor Voltage
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have one main drive motor for each traction device fulfilling the following conditions:* using 12 V voltage* using not more than 30 A current

Requirement.dc:title: Encoder Voltage
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have an encoder powered by 5 V voltage.

Requirement.dc:title: Energy Management
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have an energy management fullfilling all of the following conditions:* distributing the energy to all systems* prioritizing the energy available for the different systems* limiting energy to individual systems to prioritize individual systems* managing energy that the Mars Rover can recharge by itself in a time period of less than 24 hours

Requirement.dc:title: Motion
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself.

Requirement.dc:title: Motion over Obstacles
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself over obstacles which fullfill one of the following condition:* the obstacle is max. 20 cm high* the slope angle uphil is max. 30 degree* the slope angle downhil is max. 30 degree* the roll angle of the Mars Rover since moving over the obstacle never exceeds an angle of 30 degree

Requirement.dc:title: Deformation of the bogie
Requirement.dc:description: The bogie of the suspension system shall not bend more than 5% since all motion events.

Requirement.dc:title: Plastic deformation of the bogie
Requirement.dc:description: The bogie of the suspension system shall not deform plastically for bending less than or equal to 7%.

Requirement.dc:title: Motion Ground Contact
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall produce a ground pressure of max. 20 kPa.

Requirement.dc:title: Max Motion Speed
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself with a max. speed of 7 m/s.

Requirement.dc:title: Motion over slopes
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to move on slopes which fullfill the following condition:* slope angle uphill max. 20 degree* slope angle downhill max. 30 degree* slope angle sidehill max 15 degree

Requirement.dc:title: Electric Motion Drive
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have one left and one right traction device both driven by one electrical motor each.

Requirement.dc:title: Motion Distance
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to move at least 100m per day on all slopes where it is able to move on.

Requirement.dc:title: Min Motion Speed
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to move by itself with a min. speed of 1 m/min

Requirement.dc:title: Start Driving
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall start driving by itself on all slopes where it is able to move on.

Requirement.dc:title: Stopping
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to stop moving by itself down to 0 m/s speed.

Requirement.dc:title: Hill Holding
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall maintain 0 m/s motion on all slopes it is able to move on.

Requirement.dc:title: Steering
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to change driving direction to the left and to the right.

Requirement.dc:title: Diving Direction
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to drive forwards and backwards.

Requirement.dc:title: Navigate
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to calculate a route between its actual position and a target position

Requirement.dc:title: Detecting Obstacles
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to identify obstacles by itself

Requirement.dc:title: Map Data
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have map data stored enabling it to calculate a route between its actual position and a target position

Requirement.dc:title: Preventing Obstacles
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall prevent driving over obstacles if all of the following conditions are true:* the obstacle exceeds the measures of an acceptable obstacle as required in 1.1.3.2* a rout is available around the obstacle or rearwards to a position capable to reach the target without crossing the obstacle.

Requirement.dc:title: Remote Control
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be controllable remote.

Requirement.dc:title: Remote Steering
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover steering direction shall be controllable remote.

Requirement.dc:title: Remote Speed Control
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover speed shall be controllable remote.

Requirement.dc:title: Remote Control Priority
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover remote control shall be able to overrule the auto navigation function.

Requirement.dc:title: Optical Feedback
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall provide optical information if it is operable or not.

Requirement.dc:title: LED
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a LED for optical information if it is operable or not.

Requirement.dc:title: Max Mass
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a total mass of not more than 12 kg

Requirement.dc:title: Mars Rover Mass
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a total mass of not more than 10 kg

Requirement.dc:title: Payload
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall have a payload of 2 kg.

Requirement.dc:title: Mars Rover Capabilities
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to execute the following operations individually and not in combination:* Moving on Mars surface* Capturing optical information* Capturing video information* Capturing audio information* Sampling of Probes of solid material of individual diameter not bigger than 20 mm* Sampling of probes of fluid material in the range of ph-value 0 to 11* Sampling of probes of gas of not more than 50 mm³ volume and pressure between 1 hPa up to 3.000 hPa* Sampling of biological probes of not more than 50 mm³ volume and not more than 30 mm length in any direction

Requirement.dc:title: Mars Rover Communication
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to communicate sampled information to the Mars station.

Requirement.dc:title: Information Storage
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be capable to store information up to 2 TB

Requirement.dc:title: Sample Storage
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to store probes up to 48 h long.

Requirement.dc:title: Unloading
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to unload stored probes into the Mars Station.

Requirement.dc:title: Operating on Mars
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to operate on the planet Mars.

Requirement.dc:title: Operating Atmosphere
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to operate in Mars atmosphere for at least 25 years.

Requirement.dc:title: Mars Gravity
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to operate under Mars gravity of 3.71 m/s².

Requirement.dc:title: Mars Temperatures
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to operate in a temperature range from -80°C up to 80°C

Requirement.dc:title: Mars Radiation
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to be fully operable under constant cosmic radiation of at least 250 mSv.

Requirement.dc:title: Landing on Mars
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to land on planet Mars.

Requirement.dc:title: Landing Temperatures
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall resist temperatures of not more than 100°C for not more than 7 minutes while staying full functional.

Requirement.dc:title: Landing Deceleration
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be able to withstand landing deceleration as listed below:* Deceleration from 20.000 km/h at Mars atmosphere entry to 1.500 km/h in 4 minutes.* Deceleration from 1.500 km/s to 25 m/s in 3 minutes

Requirement.dc:title: Landing speed
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall be full operable after a landing on Mars with the following conditions beeing true:* The vertical speed at ground contact is not higher than 1 m/s* The horizontal speed at graund contact is not higher than 1 m/s

Requirement.dc:title: Landing Orientation
Requirement.dc:description: The Mars Rover shall land on Mars with the traction units first contacting the ground.
